auchenberg:
I looked into this and thought it was because BigVideo didn't use the loop-attribute on the <video>, but even with the loop-attribute set, Chrome seems to make conditional gets for the video source. 
. I had a similar need, and implemented a dispose method, which cleans up the player events, disposes the player and unbinds from resize (after it has been namespaced).
// set events
$(window).on('resize.bigvideo', function() {
    updateSize();
});
```
BigVideo.dispose = function() {
    isInitialized = false;
$(window).off('resize.bigvideo');

if(player) {
    player.off('loadedmetadata');
    player.off('ended');
    player.dispose();
}

}
``
