. Hey,
I can reproduce this with the sample file. Chrome plays fine, but Safari 8 does not. The funny bit is this: Switching the order to mp4 first, it plays in both browsers, both mp4. Now ideally you'd want Chrome to play webm and Safari mp4 after realizing it can't play the first webm source. Why it does not do this, I do not know.
Some research would point to this being a combination of: VideoJS detecting a false positive for webm on Safari, encodings of the video and the operating system support for those, order of checking supported file formats in VideoJS.
